articles.author: Parisa Hafezi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israel hit back at Iran early on Saturday, with its military saying it was conducting strikes against military targets in response to Tehran's attacks on Israel.
articles.title: Israel hits back at Iran with strikes on military targets, IDF says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Russian drone struck a multi-storey residential building in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv on Friday evening, triggering a fire in the top floors and killing one person and injuring five, officials said.
articles.title: Russian drone hits Kyiv high-rise building, kills one, injures five

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt, Gabriella Borter, Georgina Mccartney
articles.description: Kamala Harris and Donald Trump took a detour from barnstorming the battleground states that will decide November's election with Friday stops in Texas, a conservative state that was the first to implement a near-total abortion ban.
articles.title: Harris focuses on abortion in Texas, as Trump heads to Michigan

articles.author: Maya Gebeily, James Mackenzie, John Irish
articles.description: The Paris conference aims to mobilise both humanitarian aid and support for the Lebanese military.
articles.title: Israeli strike kills Lebanese troops as France rallies support for army

articles.author: Tassilo Hummel, Tom Balmforth, Maria Martinez
articles.description: Ukraine's bid to have Russia added to an international list of countries with weak money laundering compliance has failed again after the move was rejected by countries including China, India, Saudi Arabia and South Africa, three sources with knowledge of the matter told Reuters.
articles.title: Ukraine's bid to add Russia to FATF's 'black list' fails again, rejected by China, India and others

articles.author: Felix Light, Lucy Papachristou
articles.description: Georgians vote on Saturday in a parliamentary election depicted by both sides as an existential battle that will determine whether the country integrates closely with the West or leans back towards Moscow.
articles.title: Georgia votes in election seen as stark choice between Russia and West

articles.author: Jonathan Saul, James Mackenzie
articles.description: Instead of the Israeli military's preferred approach of quick decisive actions, many former security officials say the army risks being bogged down in an open-ended campaign requiring a permanent troop presence.
articles.title: With no exit strategy for Israel in Gaza, critics fear an open-ended stay

articles.author: Lucinda Elliott
articles.description: In Uruguay's capital Montevideo and around this South American nation of 3.4 million people, voters are gearing up for Sunday's election, overshadowed by a plebiscite on pensions the same day and fears over crime.
articles.title: Uruguay set for election dominated by pensions, crime

articles.author: Mike Stone, Ben Blanchard
articles.description: China has been stepping up military pressure against Taiwan, including holding a new round of war games around the island last week.
articles.title: US approves $2 billion arms sale to Taiwan including Ukraine tested missile system

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The United States was notified by Israel ahead of its operation against targets in Iran, a U.S. official told Reuters on Friday, speaking on condition of anonymity.
articles.title: US notified by Israel ahead of its strikes in Iran, US official says
